sentences.english: The 2011 year of white metal rabbit (hare, cat) is a year of great transformations.
For Jolie, one of the world's top box office stars, financial luck will be hers this year.
sentences.chinese: 全世界最賣座的女影星之一朱莉在兔年的財運就很旺。

sentences.english: First day just crossed, as soon as spring then treadonned the rabbit year threshold.
sentences.chinese: 初一剛過，春天便一腳踏進了兔年的門檻。

sentences.english: Year of the Rabbit gets Sydney hopping.
sentences.chinese: 海外華人迎新春，悉尼同胞慶兔年。

sentences.english: I am a Rabbit and the coming year is the year of the Rabbit. What does it mean for me?
sentences.chinese: 節，我的生肖是兔。兔年對我來說，有什麼意味嗎？

sentences.english: The “Year of the Rabbit” is one of the 12 zodiac symbols associated with the Chinese Lunar Calendar.
sentences.chinese: 兔年是中國陰曆中的十二生肖年之一。

sentences.english: Therefore, in the Year of the Rabbit, people worldwide can benefit from the sign that they can develop fast and be promoted.
sentences.chinese: 步入兔年，天下衆生幸藉此兆，飛速發展，步步登高。

sentences.english: Best of luck in the rabbit year to come.
sentences.chinese: 願你在未來的兔年裏，吉星高照。

sentences.english: According to the Chinese Zodiac, 2011 is the Year of the Rabbit. (February 11, 2011) (Eugene Hoshiko/Associated Press)
sentences.chinese: 根據中國生肖，2011年是兔年。

definition: Year of the Ox or Bull (e.g. 2009)
twenty-eighth year H4 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 2011 or 2071
year of one's birth sign, according to the cycle of 12 animals of the earthly branches 地支[di4 zhi1]
twenty-seventh year G3 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 2010 or 2070
